<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6357] CREATE TRIGGER doesn&apos;t detect all illegal references to SESSION schema</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6357</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The reference manual&apos;s section on the DECLARE GLOBAL TEMPORARY TABLE statement says: Temporary tables cannot be referenced in a triggered-SQL-statement&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It detects most cases and reports:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ERROR XCL51: The requested function can not reference tables in SESSION schema.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, some references are not detected if they are in a subquery. For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ij version 10.10&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; connect &apos;jdbc:derby:memory:db;create=true&apos;;&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; declare global temporary table temptable(x int) not logged;&lt;br/&gt;
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; create table t1(x int);&lt;br/&gt;
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; create table t2(b boolean);&lt;br/&gt;
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted&lt;br/&gt;
ij&amp;gt; create trigger tr1 after insert on t1 insert into t2 values exists(select * from session.temptable);&lt;br/&gt;
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This CREATE TRIGGER statement should have raised an error.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
